Well, to kind of get everybody up to date...
After coming home from my mission, I got back into school at Utah Valley State College, majoring in Music.  I started dancing again and joined the Ballroom company and did that for three more years.  I was able to visit Europe twice in that time, and eventually started teaching dance at the college.  I changed my major to history and worked on that for a while.  I started working at Utah Valley Regional Medical Center in 2001 and have been here since.  I took a break from school for a few semesters and have just started back with the new major, Community Health, as to take advantage of my experience at the hospital.  
I've really had a lot of good experiences over the past 10 years, and can't believe how fast the time has flown!  But it's given me great stories to tell.....want one, just ask   :)
And to add to everything, I just got married on the 7th of June to Amanda, who is in my pictures.  We're happy as can be and loving life!  
We met at the hospital where we both work.  It was Halloween of 2006.  I was Jack Sparrow and she was She-ra, if any of you remember who that is....Anyway, I met her at the work party and had to find out who she was.  It took me a couple of months to figure out who she was and where she worked, but I did and asked her out to a work Christmas party.  The rest is history.
